# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# kata's own state — track the canonical applied.toml so
# `kata apply` is reproducible from a fresh clone, but keep the rest
# of `.kata/` (future local-only side-files like `applied.local.toml`,
# AI transcripts, etc.) out of the repo.
/.kata/
!/.kata/applied.toml

# APM compiled outputs (committed for visibility once apm.yml exists)
# Uncomment if we change strategy:
# /.claude/skills/
# /.gemini/skills/
# /.github/skills/
# kata:gitignore:base:begin
# Editor / OS noise — kata-managed (yukimemi/pj-base).
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
# kata:gitignore:base:end


# APM dependencies
apm_modules/
